The paper deals with the problem of nodes localization in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSN), which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm uses multidimensional scaling (MDS) technique, which is a machine learning method for dimensionality reduction and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is also based on clustering, which is a common technique in the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves experiments and analysis of the algorithm's performance, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
